  "text": "In a study in this regard, Kubota et al. reported that mean SUV max of malignant mediastinal tumors was significantly higher compared to that of benign tumors. Furthermore, the cut-off value to accurately distinguish between benign and malignant mediastinal tumors was a differential uptake ratio (synonymous with SUV), which was estimated at approximately 3.5 [CITATION_1] .",
